Description copied from interface: DatumTransformation
Transforms a point in the source datum having longitude (x) in radians, latitude (y) in radians, and ellipsoidal height (z) in meters to the equivalent coordinates in the target datum.

Specified by:
forward in interface DatumTransformation
Parameters:
point - a point having x (longitude), y (latitude), and z (ellipsoidal height) components. This value will be altered within the method. The resulting value will be in reference to the target datum. Latitude and longitude are always in radians.
